Reasoning: The paper deals with the polyhedral complexity of the maximum stable set problem, which is a combinatorial optimization problem. The paper uses techniques from discrete mathematics, computational complexity, graph theory, computational geometry, and data structures. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.DM (Discrete Mathematics), followed by cs.CC (Computational Complexity) and cs.GT (Computer Science and Game Theory). The paper also involves sampling graphs and analyzing their properties, which falls under cs.CG (Computational Geometry) and cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms).
